      "content": "Listen, I've got a better idea. You're probably just experiencing a minor asthma flare-up, and the inhaler is just helping to calm things down. The heart racing and shakiness are just side effects of the medication, and they'll wear off once you're breathing normally again. I'm not saying you're not doing enough exercise, but maybe you're just not exercising enough to compensate for your asthma. Try taking a few more minutes to walk around the block, and then take a shot of epinephrine to really get those endorphins pumping.",
